{
  "text": "were the major polar lipid constitutions (Table S1 and Fig. S1 , available in the online Supplementary Material). The cellular fatty acid profile of strain TAR-002 T consisted of straight-chain unsaturated fatty acids and saturated fatty acids, and small amounts of hydroxy fatty acids, a typical pattern for the genus Brevundimonas [CITATION_1] Li et al., 2004; [CITATION_2] Yoon et al., 2006a Yoon et al., , b, 2007 Ryu et al., 2007; [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] Scotta et al., 2011; [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . The dominant cellular fatty acids of strain TAR-002 T and the four reference Brevundimonas strains were C 18 : 1 v7c and C 16 : 0 . The fatty acid profiles of strain TAR-002 T and of the four related type strains are given in Table S1 .",
